org.eclipse.rdf4j.query.resultio.sparqljson

Class AbstractSPARQLJSONParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.rdf4j.query.resultio.AbstractQueryResultParser
      • org.eclipse.rdf4j.query.resultio.sparqljson.AbstractSPARQLJSONParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    QueryResultParser
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SPARQLBooleanJSONParser, SPARQLJSONParserBase, SPARQLResultsJSONParser

    public abstract class AbstractSPARQLJSONParser
extends AbstractQueryResultParser
    Abstract base class for SPARQL Results JSON Parsers. Provides a common implementation of both boolean and tuple parsing.
    Author:
    Peter Ansell, Sebastian Schaffert

      • parseQueryResult

        public void parseQueryResult(InputStream in)
                      throws IOException,
                             QueryResultParseException,
                             QueryResultHandlerException
        Description copied from interface: QueryResultParser
        Parse the query results out of the given InputStream into the handler setup using QueryResultParser.setQueryResultHandler(QueryResultHandler).
        Parameters:
        in - The InputStream to parse the results from.
        Throws:
        IOException - If there is an exception from the InputStream.
        QueryResultParseException - If the query results are not parsable by this parser.
        QueryResultHandlerException - If the QueryResultHandler set in QueryResultParser.setQueryResultHandler(QueryResultHandler) throws an exception.
